00:18:26,969 --> 00:18:28,110
to specific choices that you made

458
00:18:28,150 --> 00:18:29,251
within Tales from the Borderlands.

459
00:18:29,932 --> 00:18:31,813
So for example, you have a friendly character,

460
00:18:31,893 --> 00:18:34,295
you can choose to help him and save his life or he dies.

461
00:18:34,835 --> 00:18:36,697
If he dies, you get a sweet shotgun

462
00:18:36,717 --> 00:18:38,098
you can play around in Borderlands 2 with,

463
00:18:38,118 --> 00:18:39,038
but if he lives, you get nothing.

464
00:18:40,437 --> 00:18:42,338
And your friend's alive, and you have to decide,

465
00:18:42,558 --> 00:18:43,478
what is more important to me?

466
00:18:43,678 --> 00:18:45,859
Is it the emotional value of my friend,

467
00:18:45,999 --> 00:18:47,860
or is it the mechanical value of this shotgun?

468
00:18:50,041 --> 00:18:51,461
What's more, every single time you played

469
00:18:51,501 --> 00:18:52,281
with that gun in Borderlands 2,

470
00:18:52,321 --> 00:18:53,702
you just had to see your dead friend's face.

471
00:18:55,002 --> 00:18:56,443
And you had to live with that decision forever.

472
00:18:56,563 --> 00:18:58,764
And everyone in the game would know what you had to do

473
00:18:59,084 --> 00:18:59,984
to get that shotgun.

474
00:19:00,004 --> 00:19:02,325
You had to be a jerk who let their friend die

475
00:19:02,505 --> 00:19:03,105
to have the shotgun.

476
00:19:03,125 --> 00:19:04,626
You just be reminded of the choice you made

477
00:19:04,686 --> 00:19:05,226
over and over again.

478
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:10,085
So this got scoped out of the game for a number of reasons, but it might sound familiar to

479
00:19:10,105 --> 00:19:13,166
a few of you who've played Mafia III because completely independent of me, this system

480
00:19:13,206 --> 00:19:16,788
was sort of designed into Mafia III within the sit-downs mechanic.

481
00:19:17,548 --> 00:19:21,930
So in Mafia III, when you complete your takeover of a specific district, a specific piece of

482
00:19:22,010 --> 00:19:26,332
the world map, you sit down with your three lieutenants, who are all criminals, and you

483
00:19:26,352 --> 00:19:28,133
decide who you're going to parcel out to.

484
00:19:28,993 --> 00:19:31,473
And all the sort of mechanical rewards in the game,

485
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:33,694
all your sort of tech trees are locked behind this mechanic.

486
00:19:33,754 --> 00:19:35,394
So each character has their own tech tree.

487
00:19:35,474 --> 00:19:36,634
One of them might give you a better gun,

488
00:19:36,994 --> 00:19:38,415
another might give you a faster car,

489
00:19:38,735 --> 00:19:40,515
or explosives, or that kind of thing.

490
00:19:41,415 --> 00:19:43,516
So if you want to dive deep into one character's tech tree,

491
00:19:43,756 --> 00:19:45,576
you had to give them a disproportionately larger

492
00:19:45,636 --> 00:19:48,217
amount of property, which eventually would piss off

493
00:19:48,717 --> 00:19:49,937
the guy who got the least property,

494
00:19:49,997 --> 00:19:51,057
and he will actually turn on you,

495
00:19:51,117 --> 00:19:51,837
and you have to fight them.

496
00:19:51,897 --> 00:19:53,738
And it's the whole thing where all of that property

